comments: Fox (SAC) reaches in and wipes away Green's (HOU) off-arm during his dribble and the contact is marginal.
Sabonis (SAC) engages and disengages with Sengun (HOU) and marginal arm contact occurs as he attempts to set the pick.
Fox (SAC) moves alongside Green's (HOU) path with a legally collapsed forearm as he contests Green's driving shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) extends his arm forward, causing marginal contact to occur with Green (HOU) during his dribble on the perimeter.
Fox (SAC) moves alongside Green's (HOU) path with a legally collapsed forearm as he contests Green's driving shot attempt.
Martin Jr. (HOU) cleanly blocks Sabonis' (SAC) shot attempt prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Fox (SAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Green (HOU) on the perimeter prior to incidental contact occurring.

Replay review of the offensive foul called on Martin Jr. pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Murray (SAC) establishes a legal guarding position in Martin Jr.'s (HOU) path prior to his upward motion and absorbs the contact in his chest during Martin Jr.'s shot attempt.
Monk (SAC) makes clean contact with the ball as he and Martin Jr. (HOU) both move toward the rebound and incidental contact occurs.
Smith Jr. (HOU) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Monk's (SAC) driving shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) steps into Sabonis' (SAC) body and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Martin Jr. (HOU) swipes and avoids making arm contact with Murray (SAC) during his put-back shot attempt.
Martin Jr. (HOU) makes clean contact with the ball, which causes Murray (SAC) to return to the floor without losing control of the ball. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
After the jump ball, Fox (SAC) and Gordon (HOU) mutually engage and disengage during the pursuit of the loose ball.
Gordon (HOU) touches the ball last before going out of bounds and it is incorrectly awarded to Houston.
Monk (SAC) commits a take foul on Gordon (HOU).
Monk (SAC) cleanly steals the ball before incidental contact occurs with Martin Jr. (HOU) during the pass.
SAC is granted a timeout immediately upon the change in possession and before Monk (SAC) dribbles the ball.
Gordon (HOU) initiates lower body contact to Fox (SAC) while he is in his shooting motion and before the expiration of time.
